==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ocelot
<hw>O"ce*lot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Mexican
<ets>ocelotl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An American feline
carnivore (<spn>Felis pardalis</spn>). It ranges from the Southwestern
United States to Patagonia. It is covered with blackish ocellated spots
and blotches, which are variously arranged. The ground color varies from
reddish gray to tawny yellow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

